12/1/2021

(methodology below)

Methodology of above chunk: - Took in data (from Energy Atlas) which included utility energy consumption data for buildings of all types, aggregated by census tract - Filtered for residential single-family homes (data included multi family, commercial, industrial, etc.) - Divided total usage by built SF to get energy intensity - mapped an individual year, then - Took average of year 2013-2017 - Mapped by energy intensity (Btu/SF), darker blue being higher

Methodology of above: - only had population for total residential (includes mutli family, etc) - but had SF data for single family homes. got percentage that single family homes make up of total residential, to multiply by the usage per capita for total residential to get usage per capita for single family homes - helps to control for neighborhoods that might have different proportions of homes vs. multifamily complexes, mobile homes, etc.
